data.name: btnStart.ToolTip
data.value: Click this to start the prompting for input file(s) and location to place output KML files after the below properties are chosen: threshold, loss factor, spatial decimation and distance, colors for pass, fail and threshold and if threshold lines should be created (recommended). After the KML files have been created, launch Google Earth then click File, then open and select all of the KML files created.

data.name: chkBxMgpsAndCsv.ToolTip
data.value: *Currently Not Available* This should be checked when a .mgps is to be used with a macat created .csv file that contains just time and power levels for a given center frequency.
